        if (Pointers[i].first->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() ==
                Pointers[j].first->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace() &&
            ECs.isEquivalent(Pointers[i].first, Pointers[j].first)) {
          PtrToGroup[j] = PtrToGroup[i];
          CheckingGroups.back().addPointer(j, *this);
        }
    ```

### 5. Conclusion

By adding the address space check, we ensure that `RuntimeCheckingPtrGroup`s are only formed from pointers within the same address space, even if they alias with pointers in other address spaces. This respects the design of `RuntimeCheckingPtrGroup` and prevents the assertion failure. The analysis will now correctly create separate checking groups for `%as3` and `%as4`, resolving the crash.
